Salomon SA, the French maker of skibindings and boots, said it is seeking a 75 mln dlreuro-commercial paper program that will be supported by a 75mln dlr committed syndicated revolving credit.    The launch of the program is still subject to finalapproval of the French authorities.    Morgan Guaranty Ltd is the arranger for the program and therevolving credit and will act as one of the dealers for thecommercial paper along with Credit Suisse First Boston Ltd.Morgan Guaranty Trust Co of New York, London branch, will beissuing and paying agent. None of the terms were disclosed. REUTER&#3;